 class=title>   PoG - Easy Solution</span><hr size=1> It's easy and pleases both sides of the coin.  <br>
Sunday-Thursday, PoG = FCFS.  <br>
Friday, PoG = off limits.  <br>
Saturday, PoG = reservable by all via the board.<br>
<br>
I realize that leaves one day for large scheduled raids, but nothing is stopping you from gettin online at 4pm, sitting at the PoG zone in, and /telling all your friends (only need about 18 of them) to come to your PoG raid that night.  <br>
<br>
Whatta you all think? <p><A HREF="http://sr.amiga.tm/" TARGET="_new"><IMG ALT="Silent Redemption Member" BORDER=0 SRC="http://fairblade.sinbad.net/images/SRlogo.gif"></A><BR><BR> Zellis the Conjurer<BR> 58 Conjurer<BR> Silent Redemption<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzestrenocya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zestrenocya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Norrath's Finest Taxi Service</span><br>  Posts: 925<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/6/01 6:40:59 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoG - Easy Solution</span><hr size=1> Countersolution since the thoughts were almost fifty fifty on the FCFS/Reservable issue.<br>
<br>
POG offlimits:  Thursday, Saturday.<br>
POG reservable: Friday, Sunday (two prime raid days instead of one.)<br>
POG FCFS: Monday/Tuesday/Wednesday<br>
<br>
But either way is good for me....I'll never be anything but a scout in there as long as I'm playing Zesty.  I believe your suggestion has merit Zellis.  Only thing that worries me is, with only one reservable &quot;prime&quot; raid day, this smacks of something that could (and probably would) end up a rotation list...and THAT is definitely something I think we'd all like to avoid.  <br>
<br>
One nice thing is that it also allows for the two day raids that some people expressed interest in.  You wouldn't have to stay out of POG on saturday if you were &quot;stepping on your own raid&quot; that was reserved for sunday.   <p><BR>
