<br>
As for the previous day being off limits to allow respawn ... I wouldn't have a problem with the person that has, say, the Sunday reserved being able to go in early on Saturday and taking two days since they are not stepping on anyone else's raid just their own.<br>
<br>
I'd also like to see it on the FCFS days if we could have it were sharing the zone with multiple small groups would be common.   Example:  Say on a Monday (FCFS day) Nillon wants to grab 5 other people and hit PoG for a few hours,  Maya wants to go in with 12 people, and Raider_00 wants to go in with 12 people.   I don't see why in a plane this big we couldn't have a bunch of &quot;mini-raids&quot; going at once.  Just PLEASE learn to talk with each other and not run to the rants <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujontann.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jontann</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 169<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/6/01 10:42:10 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/jontanneq/JonIcon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoG - Easy Solution</span><hr size=1> Up until now I've been keeping out of the whole PoG debate because I haven't gone there yet (and because I'm not convinced that I wouldn't rather have cobalt over berserker's anyhow for most pieces) and thus didn't really have any practical experience to back up my opinions.  The solution that Zellis proposed just makes too much sense, though, so I decided to chime in.  I think it's a great idea.  I'm not sure if the distribution of days is the right one, but the concept is both sound and fair to both the &quot;FCFS&quot; and the &quot;scheduled&quot; crowd.<br>
<br>
/cheer Zellis<br>
